The paper discusses the use of neural networks for end-to-end conversation modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for building intelligent dialog systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unstructured data such as Twitter and Foursquare data for external knowledge, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.SD).
